U.S. Treasury Department Schedule for Monday, May 2

-- B y   V i n c e n t   D e l   G i u d i c e
-- 
2011-05-02T12:48:42Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-05-02/u-s-treasury-department-schedule-for-monday-may-2.html
The following is a reformatted version
of the U.S. Treasury Department’s daily release on the schedule
for Secretary Timothy F. Geithner and other officials:  In the morning, Deputy Secretary Wolin will deliver keynote
remarks at the Independent Community Bankers Association’s
(ICBA) 2011  Washington  Policy Summit. The Deputy Secretary will
discuss the Dodd-Frank Act and how financial reform protects and
strengthens community banks. This event is open press.  In the evening, Secretary Geithner will attend the
President’s dinner with bipartisan leaders and ranking members,
the Vice President, other members of the Cabinet, and senior
members of the White House staff and their spouses at the White
House. This dinner is closed press.  On Monday, at 3pm, Treasury will release its current
estimates of marketable borrowing in advance of the Treasury
Borrowing Committee (TBAC) meeting on Tuesday. Additional
financing details relating to Treasury’s Quarterly Refunding
will be released at 10am on Wednesday, May 4.  To contact the reporter on this story:
Vincent Del Giudice in Washington 
 vdelgiudice@bloomberg.net .  To contact the editor responsible for this story:
Christopher Wellisz at   cwellisz@bloomberg.net  